<pdd-reason>Generate a small parser utility with validation and tests-friendly behavior.</pdd-reason>
<pdd-interface>
parse_kv_lines(text: str) -> dict[str, str]
format_kv_pairs(items: dict[str, str]) -> str
</pdd-interface>

Build a Python module for key/value configuration snippets.

Rules:
- parse_kv_lines accepts newline-separated lines in the form key=value.
- Blank lines and lines beginning with # are ignored.
- Keys are stripped and must be non-empty.
- Values are stripped but may be empty.
- Duplicate keys raise ValueError naming the key.
- Lines without = raise ValueError naming the 1-based line number.
- format_kv_pairs emits keys in sorted order as key=value lines joined by "\n".
- Do not perform file I/O.
